nunbushyeo, Baby
i jomyeong, Shining
We’re in love with this carnival

sashil museoweo nan

snippet.title: NCT WISH 엔시티 위시 'TAP' + 'Smoothie' @Practice Room
snippet.description:
여러분~~~ 저희가 쇼! 음악중심 in JAPAN에서 엔시티 선배님들의 무대를 준비했는데요!! 저희가 존경하는 선배님들, 노래들이라 더 재밌게 열심히 연습했으니까 많이 기대해주시온💚 베르나돔에서 무대는 처음이었는데 너무 재밌었어요😎💚

みなさん〜！Show! Music Core in JAPANでNCT先輩たちのステージを準備しました！！ 僕たちが尊敬する先輩たちの歌なので、いつもよりもっと楽しく一生懸命練習しました！たくさん期待してください💚 ベルーナドームでの舞台は初めてでしたが、とても面白かったです😎💚

snippet.title: 세탁,주방,식기세척기,화장실까지 깨끗이 쓸어왔다.. 73% 할인율로 닦아온 각종 세제 네고 [네고왕] Ep.20
snippet.description:
09:09 개구리 부장님

네고왕이 해온 스무번째 네고 = 각종 세제 🫧

1.알로에베라 세탁세제 1.5L 4개 = 22,800원
 
2.알로에베라 세탁세제 1.5L 1개 = 6,000원
 
3.알로에베라 세탁세제 1.5L 2개 + 알로에베라 섬유유연제 750ml 1개 + 얼룩제거제 500ml 1개 = 18,800원
*5,000세트 한정 수량
 
4.올인원 식기세척기 세제 1박스(30개입) = 6,900원
*베이킹소다, 그린레몬 중 택1 / 50,000세트 한정 수량
 
5.주방세제 500ml 1개 = 3,500원
*라즈베리, 베이킹소다, 레드오렌지, 레몬민트, 알로에베라 중 택1 / 70,000세트 한정 수량
 
6.물때제거용 클리너 500ml 1개 + 변기세정제 750ml 1개 = 9,900원
*라즈베리 단일 진행 / 10,000세트 한정 수량
 
*ID당 세탁세제,주방세제 2개 / 그 외 1개 구매제한
*기간 : 7일(7/11-7/17)
*구매 : 카카오 쇼핑하기
*배송 : 15,000원 이상 무료배송

네고왕 홍현희
개구리왕 김정숙

[자세한 네고]
더 자세한 사항은 하단의 안내 링크에서 확인해 주세요.
https://kko.to/PSla_jJMwZ

더 크고 더 쎄진 리얼 협상 예능 [네고왕]
👑 매주(목) 저녁 6시 30분
👑 구독+댓글+알림설정ㄱㄱ
 
#네고왕 #홍현희 #각종세제
#달라스튜디오 #네고왕6 #Negoking

snippet.title: "진짜 대형사고 나겠다"…난리 난 성수역 상황 / SBS / 뉴블더
snippet.description:
최근 서울 성수동이 이른바 핫플레이스로 떠올랐죠.

각종 팝업 스토어와 카페들, 그리고 기업들이 들어서면서 유동 인구도 급증했는데요.

동시에 성수역에 인파가 몰리면서 안전사고를 우려하는 목소리도 커지고 있습니다.

서울 성동구의 성수역 3번 출구 앞입니다.

사람들이 끝도 없이 줄지어 서 있고, 건물을 돌아 다음 사거리까지 줄은 이어져 있습니다.

모두 퇴근길 지하철을 타려는 사람들입니다.

매번 몰리는 퇴근길 인파에 대형 안전사고를 우려하는 시민 목소리도 터져 나옵니다.

[성수역 인근 직장인 : 평일 매일매일은 퇴근 시간에 항상 그 정도고, 개찰구부터 외부 밖에 상가까지 줄 서 있고요, 승강장도 꽉 차 있어요. 아무래도 밀지 말라는 얘기도 하시고, 다칠 것 같다고 천천히 와라 이렇게 하시는 경우도 많이 봤고요. 진짜 밀려서 넘어지면 크게 누가 다칠 수도 있겠다 라는 생각은 항상 하면서 퇴근을 해요. (사람이) 좀 빠지는 거 보고 카페에 있다가 퇴근하는 것 같아요.]

공업단지였던 성수동에 각종 팝업 스토어가 들어오고, 기업들도 많아지며 유동 인구가 늘어난 영향입니다.

실제로 성수역의 하루 평균 승하차 인원은 3년 사이에 50% 가까이 늘었습니다.

하지만 역이 지어진 지난 1980년 이후, 눈에 띄는 변화는 없었고 여전히 출입구는 4곳뿐이라 늘어난 인파를 감당하기 어렵게 된 겁니다.

역 개선이 필요하다는 지적도 이어집니다.

[이수범/서울시립대 교통공학과 교수 : 진입하는 용량을 늘려줘야 하는데 계단을 좀 더 넓게 하거나, 아니면 조금 빠른 에스컬레이터를 설치를 하거나 개찰구를 조금 더 개수를 늘려서 사람들이 빨리빨리 많이 플랫폼으로 갈 수 있게끔 하거나 이런 방식이 필요할 것이라고 봅니다. 출입구를 새로 하나 개설하는 부분에 대해서도 좀 신중하게 검토할 필요는 있죠.]

성동구청도 대책을 내놨는데요.

일단 평일 출퇴근 시간대에 사람이 쏠리는 성수역 2·3번 출구 앞에 안전요원을 2명씩 배치하겠다고 밝혔습니다.

다만 당장 지하철 출입구를 늘리는 건 어렵다는 입장입니다.

지난 2021년부터 서울시와 서울교통공사에 성수역 출구 신설을 꾸준히 요청하고 있지만, 타당성 조사 결과 사업성이 낮아 어렵다는 통보를 받았다는 게 성동구청의 설명입니다.

그래도 연말까지 타당성 조사를 다시 실시해서 의미 있는 결과를 낼 수 있도록 노력하겠다고 밝혔습니다.

(영상편집 : 문이진)

snippet.title: [단독] "이러다 큰일날까봐 겁이 나"...사람보다 개들이 더 많은 '그 집'｜이상엽의 부글터뷰
snippet.description:
지난 5월 경기 부천시의 한 빌라 집주인은 60대 남성에게 70㎡(21평)짜리 방을 내줬습니다. 그런데 이삿날부터 이웃과의 갈등이 시작됐습니다. 밤낮으로 개 짖는 소리 때문에 주민들이 불편을 겪는 겁니다. 이른바 '층견소음' 갈등에 경찰도 수차례 출동했지만 소용없었다고 했습니다. 현장에서 무슨 일이 벌어지는 걸까요? JTBC 디지털콘텐트기획 '이상엽의 부글터뷰'에서 남성을 오래 설득한 끝에 집 안을 직접 살펴봤습니다.

localized.title: [단독] "이러다 큰일날까봐 겁이 나"...사람보다 개들이 더 많은 '그 집'｜이상엽의 부글터뷰
localized.description:
지난 5월 경기 부천시의 한 빌라 집주인은 60대 남성에게 70㎡(21평)짜리 방을 내줬습니다. 그런데 이삿날부터 이웃과의 갈등이 시작됐습니다. 밤낮으로 개 짖는 소리 때문에 주민들이 불편을 겪는 겁니다. 이른바 '층견소음' 갈등에 경찰도 수차례 출동했지만 소용없었다고 했습니다. 현장에서 무슨 일이 벌어지는 걸까요? JTBC 디지털콘텐트기획 '이상엽의 부글터뷰'에서 남성을 오래 설득한 끝에 집 안을 직접 살펴봤습니다.

snippet.title: “저희는 절대 저렇게 멀쩡한 아이를 안락사시키지 않아요” 마을 어르신들을 공포에 떨게 한 개의 진짜 속마음 │세상에 나쁜 개는 없다│알고e즘
snippet.description:
이번 주 ‘세상에 나쁜 개는 없다(이하 세나개)‘의 주인공은 검고 새빨간 눈에 맹수의 기질을 보유한 카네 코르소 ’헌터‘다. 이탈리아에서는 마피아 견으로 이용되는 경비견 중 하나다.

헌터가 살고 있는 곳은 전북의 한 시골 마을이다. 이 곳 주민의 평균 연령은 65세로 고령의 어르신들이 많이 살고 계신다. 지나가는 마을 어르신들만 보면 거칠게 달려드는 탓에 헌터는 마을의 공포견이 되고 말았다. 그러던 어느 날, 헌터가 동네 주민을 물었다는 소문이 돌자 헌터는 마을 주민들 사이에서 위험한 개로 낙인이 찍히게 되었다.

조용한 시골 마을을 뒤흔든 공포견이 위기에 처했다는 사연을 듣고 설채현 전문가 찾아왔다. 희대의 공포견 헌터를 만난 설 전문가는 의미심장한 한 마디를 건넨다. “헌터는 나쁜 개가 아니에요.” 모두를 충격에 빠트린 설 전문가의 말의 의미는 무엇일까?

헌터가 한 때 안락사 위기에 처했었다는 딱한 사연에 이어, 헌터를 오해했던 마을 주민들과 함께 해서 더 뜻깊고 특별했던 솔루션이 공개된다.

#EBS #알고e즘 #세나개 #세상에나쁜개는없다 #개 #강아지 #반려견 #카네코르소 #마피아견 #시골 #시골개 #공포견 #설채현 #수의사 

📺방송정보

📌방송일자: 2018년 6월 1일

snippet.title: 유리 파편이 지천에 깔린 폐공장에서 모기 유충이 가득한 썩은 물을 마시며 사는 어미견과 새끼견들을 구조한 설채현 수의사│세상에 나쁜 개는 없다│알고e즘
snippet.description:
유리 파편 가득한 공장 주변에서 지내던 진돗개 가족

배우 김혜선 씨의 가족이 되다

공장 부지에 출산한 지 얼마 안 돼 보이는 진돗개 어미가 새끼들을 보살피고 있다는 제보를 받고 도착한 이곳, 공장 주변엔 낭떠러지로 둘러싸여 있고 바닥엔 유리 파편이 가득한데... 공장을 이전하면서 많은 폐기물이 쌓여 있는 상태. 생후 50일 정도의 진돗개 새끼들이 폐기물들을 옮기는 중장비 차들 사이를 오가며 음식물 쓰레기를 주워 먹고 있는데...

주변에 수소문을 해보니, 그동안 공장 사람들이 챙겨주는 먹이를 먹으며 어미 진돗개는 40여 마리의 새끼를 낳았다고 한다. 하지만 이제는 공장이 이전되며 이들을 챙겨줄 수 없게 됐다는데... 사람 키보다 깊은 낭떠러지로 둘러싸여 새끼들이 언제라도 아래로 떨어질 수 있는 위험 상황. 또한 어미 개가 모기 유충이 가득한 물을 먹고 있어, 혹시 심장사상충 같은 위험한 질병에 걸리진 않았을까 우려가 된다. 열악한 환경에서 새끼들부터 챙기는 진한 모성애를 보여주는 어미 진돗개와 아직 꼬물꼬물한 새끼 진돗개들의 생생한 구조 현장이 공개된다.

그리고 모성애 가득한 진돗개 가족의 사연에 감동한 배우 김혜선 씨가 세.나.개에 함께 했다! 평소 애견인이었던 김혜선 씨가 우연히 이 소식을 전해 듣고, 진돗개 가족의 입양을 결정하게 됐다고 하는데... 김혜선 씨를 보자마자 따르는 진돗개 가족들의 아름다운 감동 스토리! 
#유기견 #공장 #물 #썩은물 #유리 #파편 #위험 #구조 #설채현 #설쌤 #알고e즘  #감동

snippet.description:
바람같이 찾아온 봄이의 犬.춘.기!
 
밥을 먹다가도, 거실에서 쉬다가도
갑자기 가족들을 향해 드러내는
사.나.운. 이.빨.
 
봄이의 마음을 알 수 없는 가족들 ..
거실을 두고 봄이와 가족 사이의 거리는
점점 멀어져만 가는데 ㅠㅠ
 
과연 봄이에게 무슨 사연이 있는 걸까?

About UFOs: Investigating the Unknown
In 2021, the US government passed legislation mandating an official investigation into UFOs. This provocative series unspools the history leading up to this momentous change and reports on recent developments. It explores what the government made public versus what was kept hidden; citizens' push for transparency while confronting mass UFO sightings; Navy pilots' reports of unexplainable technology; new cutting-edge scientific efforts; and what the future might hold for this confounding mystery which is the focus of a deepening and expanding search for answers.

snippet.title: Giant UFO in Texas (Full Episode) | UFOs: Investigating the Unknown
snippet.description:
In 2008 in Stephenville, Texas a local pilot sees lights in the sky over his ranch coming from something huge. He is not alone: hundreds of people saw the craft, and a local reporter makes it her life’s work to tell their stories. From this classic encounter we head back several decades to the beginning of the UFO phenomenon in America and the launch of Project Blue Book to study the country’s growing “UFO problem.”

snippet.title: Global National: July 11, 2024 | Biden mixes up Harris, Trump in 1st press conference since debate
snippet.description:
In tonight’s top story: A growing chorus of once-friendly Democratic voices continues to turn against U.S. President Joe Biden, in the wake of a disastrous debate that has raised concerns about Biden’s health and age. In another big test for the U.S. president, Biden stepped up to the podium in a post-NATO summit news conference, where he faced open questions from the press for the first time since his now infamous debate showing — and raised even more alarm. Jackson Proskow has more.

On the final day of the NATO summit, Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has now revealed that Canada plans to hit NATO’s defence spending target of two per cent of GDP by 2032. Right now, the country spends around 1.73 per cent, and has been taking heat from allies for not meeting the mark. Despite the pledge, Trudeau questioned the relevance of the target for Canada, saying that “...we continually step up and punch above our weight, something that isn't always reflected in the crass mathematical calculation that certain people turn to very quickly.” Mercedes Stephenson take a look.

A major development in the case of a confessed Canadian serial killer. Jeremy Skibicki has been found guilty of first-degree murder in the deaths of four Indigenous women. Justice Glenn Joyal says the murders were planned and deliberate and the facts of the case were "mercilessly graphic." Skibicki's racially-motivated killing spree has had a profound impact, and once again highlights the crisis of missing and murdered Indigenous women and girls. Melissa Ridgen reports.
 
Delegates to the annual meeting of the Assembly of First Nations (AFN) in Montreal heard from two federal party leaders on Thursday: Conservative leader Pierre Poilievre and the NDP’s Jagmeet Singh. The Conservative leader's message has been called one of “economic reconciliation,” with Poilievre saying that Indigenous peoples' relationship with the Canadian government would be one of partnership and freedom under his leadership. But one group in the audience stood and turned their backs as Poilievre spoke, in response to when he told a radio station in 2008 that he felt Indigenous people needed the values of hard work, independence and self-reliance. Mike Armstrong reports.
   
Plus, a group of independent human rights experts warned this week that famine has spread throughout the enclave. Israeli officials responded by saying the statement amounted to "misinformation." A WHO team shared images of a visit to field hospitals in Deir Balah and Khan Younis, where access to medical care, food and shelter has been a struggle for the past nine months. Those who have managed to survive are continuously displaced by intense fighting. Crystal Goomansingh has the details.

Canada’s head coach had positive news about captain Alphonso Davies, who hobbled off the pitch in the 71st minute Tuesday after a hard Argentine challenge. The team is set to play in Charlotte, N.C., on Saturday for the Copa America  third-place game against No. 14 Uruguay, which lost 1-0 to No. 12 Colombia in Wednesday's semifinal. Mackenzie Gray has more.

And finally, a simple trip to the beach became a castaway nightmare for one woman in Japan who spent 37 hours adrift in the Pacific Ocean after she was swept out to sea in an inflatable swim ring, local officials said. The woman, a Chinese national in her 20s who has not been named, was rescued on Wednesday more than 80 kilometres off the coast of Japan. Heidi Petracek explains.

For more info, please go to https://globalnews.ca

snippet.title: All eyes on Biden’s press conference as Obama and Pelosi express concern behind closed doors
snippet.description:
Catch up on CNN's coverage and analysis of President Joe Biden's critical press conference after the NATO summit.  #CNN #news 

00:00-09:31 CNN's Kaitlan Collins and her panel of experts discuss the key moments and takeaways from the press conference.
09:32-13:10 CNN's Gary Tuchman speaks with voters in Michigan about the press conference. 
13:11-20:39 Collins speaks with Rep. Jim Himes (D-CT) who announced after the press conference concluded that Biden should step down from the presidential race.
20:39-27:03 CNN's Anderson Cooper, Jeff Zeleny and David Chalian discuss new CNN reporting that former President Barack Obama and former Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi had met to discuss Biden's future.

snippet.title: President Biden holds solo press conference after NATO summit | Special Report
snippet.description:

snippet.title: The Celestial Toymaker Explained
snippet.description:
The Celestial Toymaker is among the most powerful and most cunning of the Doctor's foes, despite only ever appearing in a single Serial that was nearly all but lost to time and  the bbc's habbit of destroying their old shows. Despite this the Celestial Toymaker has made a significant impact on doctor who, through the novel adaptations, the comics and the audios, and he's coming back for the 60th so I guess I should make a video about him.

snippet.title: You're Wrong About the Valeyard
snippet.description:
I have 100 subscribers! 100 people who have decided they want to see the content that I make hours making. Thank you so much. I really do appreciate it!

The valeyard is not the doctor. He is of the doctor. Initially they were supposed to be a future doctor out to extend their life by any means necessary, but, because of behind the scenes drama he is an amalgimation of the darker sides of their nature, from somewhere between their 12th and final incarnation. And people have lost their sanity in the vain attempt to make that make sense. Heres a video essay where I do exactly that.

Subscribe to the confession dial. I used footage from one of their videos without asking but could you blame me? Click the link below to see what im talking about.
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDyk6BykMV6qBSfTNNotgBw

snippet.title: A Quick Guide to the Divergent Arc
snippet.description:
The divergent arc was big finish's grand experiment. Taking the doctor out of the whoniverse and depositing him in a universe where time travel isn't a thing. SOmething that causes a time lord pain literally and figeratively. 
it was sadly cut short on account new who returning and them realising that experimental wank was only really apealing to specific parts of the fandom that weren't new who fans, but this was truly the last great horrah of the wilderness years and contains one of the best stories that bigfinish has ever committed to audio, so its pretty good all considered.

As usual all these stories are available on spotify for free in australia and the UK and they are fairly cheap on the bigfinish website so if weird experimental shit appeals to you give them a listen.

Fan art used in this is by the amazing JohannesVIII Art. Check out their YouTube channel
https://youtube.com/@johannesviiiart6574?si=_5alWIo69EZB4ROj

Check out my brother's channel at 
https://www.youtube.com/@geoff2o9

snippet.title: The last of the 8th doctor Monthlies: Part 1
snippet.description:
I had no idea what to call this one and it seems im not alone in that. This is the last of the monthly plays for the 8th doctor . 8 stories, less serialised, designed to wrap things up with charley and C'rizz to make way for the new eth doctor adventures range more geared to new who fans. Some of them are good, some of them are very good, but then theres ones that had me ranting about blue tits of all things, and im taking them 4 at a time. this is part 1 them is so bad that I had to go on a rant about blue tits, and im taking them 4 at a time.

snippet.title: The last of the 8th doctor Monthlies: Part 2
snippet.description:
I've finally made it. the last lot of 8th doctor monthly plays and the end of an era. Sorry about the long gap between uploads. Between the terrible flu season and so many people getting sick at work ive had very little time to work on these silly little videos that i love doing so much. As I write this i am very over tired, but hey, enjoy the video. I couldnt record it all at once so if you listen closely you can hear me recovering from a sore throat.

snippet.title: A Quick Guide to the Eighth Doctor Adventures: Series 1, Part 1
snippet.description:
The 8th doctor adventures was big finish's soft reboot of the 8th doctor to appeal to fans of new who, after the iconic series returned to our screens in 2005. Taking cues from Davies who, they streamlined the series, giving it a shorter run time, less experimentation and a companion from modern day UK who is like a combination of two of the most iconic new who companions before one of them was fully a thing. 

THe took a chance with this series but they managed to create something that fans of old and new who alike can find common ground on and by far my favourite series from big finish.

Music:
Scheming Weasel faster, by Kevin MacLeod are licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 license. https://creativecommons.org/licenses/...

Hyperfun,  by Kevin MacLeod are licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 license. https://creativecommons.org/licenses/...

Footage and audio assets used is owned by the bbc and big finish.

snippet.title: E384 Our Need for Belonging with Sarah Westfall
snippet.description:
In all of the conversation around identity, relationships, loneliness, doubt, there is a key word. That word is belonging. Belonging is packed with so much meaning because it can impact or influence us personally and relationally. It is a fundamental human need to be known, to feel belonging, but that is true of what you think about yourself as much as it is what you think of your place with others. We’ve talked about identity on this podcast, and we’ve talked about relationships. Today, we’re going to focus on bridging these two topics through reimaging who we are and how we relate. 

In today's episode, host Jason Wieland is joined by Sarah Westfall, host of the Human Together podcast and author of the new book "The Way of Belonging." In this conversation, Sarah and Jason talk about the fundamental questions we wrestle with about identity, belonging and relationships, the struggles that try to keep us from feeling rooted in our belonging, how the journey to know God is also a journey to know ourselves, and what it means to reimagine who we are and how we relate. 

Doable Discipleship is a Saddleback Church podcast produced and hosted by Jason Wieland. It premiered in 2017 and now offers more than 380 episodes. Episodes release every Tuesday on your favorite podcast app and on the Saddleback Church YouTube Channel (https://www.youtube.com/saddleback).
 
Doable Discipleship is a proud part of the Saddleback Family of Podcasts. To learn more about the Saddleback Family of Podcasts, visit saddleback.com/podcasts.

The Way of Belonging - https://www.amazon.com/Way-Belonging-Reimagining-Who-Relate/dp/151400853X/

snippet.title: Learn How To Be Set Free From Self-Destruction with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
You are your biggest enemy. There are things you do in your life that frequently cause you hurt, stress, pain, unhappiness, and unnecessary pressure. Pastor Rick Warren calls them the “seven weapons of self-destruction.” In this message, he identifies what those seven weapons are and talks about how the Spirit of God can give you the antidote to every one. You’ll learn seven mental habits that will help you apply the truths in Romans 8 and defeat the weapons of self-destruction. (Sermon by Rick Warren of Saddleback Church ) 


Get connected with one of 13 Saddleback Church Campuses at http://www.saddleback.com/locations

Connect with our Online Campus and watch the messages from home http://www.saddleback.com/online or check out our Saddleback Church channel on ROKU.

snippet.title: Learn How To Recognize God's Voice with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
God wants to speak to you — but how do you know whether an idea you get in your mind is from him? Pastor Rick Warren teaches seven ways to test your ideas, impressions, and thoughts to know with absolute certainty you are hearing the voice of God. Ask yourself these questions: Does it agree with the bible? Does it make me more like Christ? Does my church family confirm it? Is it consistent with how God shaped me? Does it concern my responsibility? It is convicting rather than condemning? Do I sense God's peace about it? Pastor Rick explains all of these questions and more in this message. 


Connect to our Online Community at http://www.saddleback.com/online or find a campus near you at http://www.saddleback.com/locations --We have a place for you!

snippet.title: Learn How To Overcome Your Failures Through God's Mercy with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://www.saddleback.com/MiracleofMercy — Because we’re imperfect people that live in an imperfect world, we all experience failure in life. The night Jesus was arrested, two of his best friends had massive failures: Judas betrayed Jesus, and Peter denied him three times. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Rick Warren looks at how God’s mercy helps us overcome and move through our failures. He examines the differing responses between Peter and Judas to failure. You will discover the answer to three key questions: What causes personal failure? What should I do when I fail? And what does Jesus do when I fail?



Join a Miracle of Mercy small group and study God's mercy with others. Visit http://saddleback.com/miracleofmercy to learn more. 

Connect with our Online community throughout the week. Visit http://www.saddleback.com/online

snippet.title: How To Overcome Persistent Temptations with Rick Warren & Tom Holladay
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/rethinkyourlife — We often get stuck in the same pattern when we’re tempted: good intentions, failure, and guilt. Maybe there are areas of your life you have habitually stumbled in, and you’re wondering how to get out of this cycle. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren shares that the key to overcoming temptation is not to resist it, but to rethink how you actually see temptation.

snippet.title: How To Keep Your Tank Filled Up Instead of Running On Empty with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/margin — When you drive, how low do you let the gas tank get before you fill it up? Have you ever run out of gas, even when the warning light told you that you were running on empty? In this message, Pastor Rick gives us 10 reasons we run out of gas, and how those reasons parallel our own lives. You’ll learn how to start your day with a full tank, watch your gauges, recognize your limits, and allow time to refuel. Find out how to keep your tank filled by giving up control, learning to trust Jesus, and starting every day topped off with the right fuel. Don’t miss this final message concluding our series, Living with Margin.


Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

snippet.title: Learn How Your Understanding of God Influences How You Pray with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/pray40 — Have you ever experienced a stressful or difficult time that left you questioning the presence of God? Sometimes it takes days, months, or even years before we realize that God used that experience as an opportunity to rely on him through difficult times. The more we begin to understand what God is really like, the more everything can fall into place, including our prayer life. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren shares how God’s plan will always be good. You’ll learn how he is the good God of second chances and why he doesn’t always say “yes.” Discover everlasting encouragement and renewed strength for the days ahead.


To learn more about the 40 Days of Prayer small groups study, visit http://saddleback.com/pray40


To sign up to receive 40 Days of Prayer devotions, visit http://saddleback.com/pray40devos


If you would like to become a part of an online small group for the study, please email the Online Team at online@saddleback.com or visit http://saddleback.com/online

snippet.title: How To Pray For Healing And Restoration with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/pray40 — Does God heal people today? Of course he does! God uses different ways to heal different kinds of pain: financial, physical, mental, emotional, relational, and physical. Because we live in a broken world, we all need some kind of healing or restoration, whether we’re aware of it or not. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren teaches us four conditions for healing and restoration in any area of our lives. Learn why humility, prayer, seeking God, and reliance on his Word will bring healing and forgiveness. 




Watch more messages from 40 Days of Prayer message series and discover how to unleash the power of prayer in your life: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AKo-43Iv90uyeeo3qTBwgQV

Connect with our online community by finding a small group, taking CLASS 101, or joining our Facebook group at http://saddleback.com/online or email online@saddleback.com

snippet.title: Learn How to Pray in Five Dimensions with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/pray40  — Do you ever feel like your memory is slipping or that you have a hard time remembering things? In this message, Pastor Rick Warren teaches us the relationship between memory and prayers and what the Bible says about this deep connection. Researched from 900 different Bible verses, this sermon will teach you how to change the way you talk to God. Discover how praying in five dimensions can awaken your faith with a new freshness that is personal, passionate, and in partnership with the Holy Spirit. Get ready to take your faith to the next level by looking back to the cross, inward at Jesus living inside you, and forward to your future in Christ.



Connect with our online community by finding a small group, taking CLASS 101, or joining our Facebook group at http://saddleback.com/online or email online@saddleback.com

snippet.title: "A Faith That Can Heal Illnesses" with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
As followers of Jesus, we don’t only care about people’s spiritual needs — we care about their physical needs, as well. In fact, a major element of Jesus’ ministry on Earth was physical healing. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren continues our study through the Book of James by explaining three mistaken views about physical healing and by describing how to pray for healing for yourself and others.

You’ll learn the seven keys to praying throughout the day that will bring you closer to God and help you face any problem with spiritual confidence. Get ready to turn your scheduled prayers into habitual conversations with your heavenly Father.


Watch more messages from 40 Days of Prayer message series and discover how to unleash the power of prayer in your life: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AKo-43Iv90uyeeo3qTBwgQV

snippet.title: How To Keep From Stressing Out with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
Studies show personal stress is at near-record levels. Pastor Rick Warren of Saddleback Church looks at Paul’s anti-stress recipe in the book of Philippians and teaches five things you can do to personally experience God’s peace regardless of your circumstances. If you want to lower the stress in your life, listen to the promises that God gives in Philippians 4:6-13. In this message, you're learn how to live a life filled with God's peace and a less-stressed mind. Who doesn't want that? Check out this message. 




We are better together. Join us at one of our Southern California Campuses or at one of our four international campuses around the world. To find a location near you, visit: http://www.saddleback.com/locations

snippet.title: Learn How To Replace Your Fears With Faith with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/comebacks — Have you ever watched a football game when the underdog came back to win in the final seconds? We all love a good comeback story, especially when it results in an unexpected victory. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren shares the four truths about setbacks and how every challenge is a setup for a great comeback. You’ll learn the common fears associated with setbacks, including inadequacy, disapproval, disappointment, and loss of control. Find out how to replace fear with faith by surrendering to God and basing your hope on the promises of God.




Listen to other messages in the "Turning Setbacks Into Comebacks" series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AIx4t72BDWUNMyRRTD0iqVl&disable_polymer=true

Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: How To Fight Discouragement with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/comebacks — It’s always easier to start something than it is to finish it — college courses, construction projects, and even fitness goals. Just like a marathon, as time goes on it becomes harder to cross the finish line because of setbacks that often leave us feeling defeated. Did you know that setbacks are actually part of the character-building process designed by God? In this message, Pastor Rick Warren discusses the causes of discouragement that lead to fatigue, frustration, fear, and a sense of failure. Find out what to do when you’re ready to give up, starting with reorganizing your life, refocusing on God, and resisting discouragement. 



Listen to other messages in the "Turning Setbacks Into Comebacks" series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AIx4t72BDWUNMyRRTD0iqVl&disable_polymer=true

Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: How To Come Back From Emotional Burnout with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/comebacks — One of the common negative side effects of setbacks is that they can drain your emotional tank, leaving you feeling empty so that you have no reserves for dealing with daily life. When you feel like you have nothing left to give, each day feels as if you’re running on fumes. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren takes a look at the setbacks in Elijah’s life, and the 10 warning signs of an emotionally empty tank. You’ll learn what steps God uses to refill your life with hope, joy, and love. Discover how to find rest, release, and refocusing through Christ. 



Listen to other messages in the "Turning Setbacks Into Comebacks" series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AIx4t72BDWUNMyRRTD0iqVl&disable_polymer=true

Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: What To Do When A Setback Is Not Your Fault with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/comebacks — Budget cuts, car accidents, natural disasters, health problems — we’ve all faced setbacks in life that were outside of our control. Even the apostle Paul was pounded by angry waves and shipwrecked on his way to share God’s Word. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren tells us common mistakes that lead people into the storm and how to anchor your ship before it sinks. You’ll learn which setbacks will cause you to drift away from your goals and how to stay focused on things with eternal value. Discover the three anchors of hope founded on God’s presence, purpose, and promise!



Listen to other messages in the "Turning Setbacks Into Comebacks" series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AIx4t72BDWUNMyRRTD0iqVl&disable_polymer=true

Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online


Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: What To Do When Others Set You Back with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/comebacks — Have you ever wondered why you have so many setbacks in life? Are you waiting for a happy ending to all the suffering and challenges? In this message, Pastor Rick Warren tells us about a series of painful setbacks in Joseph’s life and how God used them to position Joseph for a spectacular comeback that saved two nations. You’ll learn how to follow his example of resilience by depending on God’s presence no matter where you are, and trusting his plan regardless of how long it takes. Don’t miss this encouraging message that will help you lean on God’s help in every challenge that comes your way!

Listen to other messages in the "Turning Setbacks Into Comebacks" series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLgmRz0Ecn4AIx4t72BDWUNMyRRTD0iqVl&disable_polymer=true

Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: Learn What To Do When You're Asked to Do the Impossible with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/unshakable — What do you do when you’re asked to do something that seems impossible? If you don’t have a clear course of action, it’s easy to become paralyzed with inaction. But God doesn’t want these impossible tasks to cause us to give up — he wants us to use these moments to build our trust in him. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Rick Warren shares a message called When You’re Asked to Do the Impossible. You’ll learn how you can respond when faced with an impossible task and rise to meet the challenge.





Connect with our Online Community throughout the week at http://saddleback.com/online.

snippet.title: Learn What To Do When The Heat Is On with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/unshakable — Everyone goes through testing. It’s a natural part of life and growth. Going through testing is rarely pleasant, but knowing God is always by your side in the midst of those challenges provides comfort and hope. Every time God sees you faithfully navigate the tests of life, he pours more blessing on your life. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Rick Warren shares a message called When the Heat is On. You’ll learn what steps you can take when you feel like you’re being pushed to violate your values.



Connect with our online community during the week at http://saddleback.com/online.

snippet.title: Learn What To Do When God Tests You With Success with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/unshakable — We all want to be successful. But often, we forget that God can use our success to test our true motives. When we achieve success in our lives, we can either praise God for what he’s done, or become proud and take the credit ourselves. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Rick Warren shares a message called When God Tests You with Success. snippet.title: "What to Remember When Things Don’t Go Your Way" with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
No matter your age, you’ve probably realized by now that most things in life don’t go your way. When things didn’t go Jonah’s way, he grew resentful toward God. In this message, Pastor Rick Warren will take you through some of the mistakes that Jonah made while trying to live out his life mission. Then, he’ll give you four important truths to remember when your life doesn’t go according to plan.

snippet.title: Choose To Manage Your Mind with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/rethinkyourlife — Have you ever noticed that your mind doesn’t want to obey you? That’s why it’s important to learn how to manage your mind. Because our thoughts control our life, our mind is a battleground for sin, but it’s also the key to peace and happiness. In this message with Pastor Rick Warren, you’ll learn about three choices you must make every day for a healthy mind.

Continue the conversation online with our Saddleback Church online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: Transformed: Change Your Life By Changing Your Mind with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
www.saddleback.com/transformed --Learn how to change your life by changing the way you think in this message from our weekend series: 50 Days of Transformation. This series is centered around our Transformed study with Pastor Rick Warren at Saddleback Church. 

This message will teach you how to change the way you think by the renewing of your mind. God is far more interested in changing your mind than in changing your circumstances. There's a battle for your mind and it's going on every day. Your mind is your greatest asset and satan wants to control your mind. Learn the three daily choices for a healthy mind and find the key to peace and happiness. God didn't bring you here to watch everyone else's life be transformed--Join in at www.saddleback.com/transformed 

For service times & locations, visit saddleback.com. Connect with our online community at saddleback.com/online.

snippet.title: Transformed: From Stressed To Blessed with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
www.saddleback.com/transformed   In this week's message from our series: 50 Days of Transformation, Pastor Rick Warren teaches on how to take us from stressed to blessed by transforming our Physical Health. The seven most common sources of stress include: worry, hurry, crowds, more choices than ever before, the loss of privacy, pluralism, and fear of the future. The seven anecdotes can all be found in Psalm 23. Learn how to lower the stress in your life in this lesson.

snippet.title: Transformed: How To Deal With How You Feel with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
www.saddleback.com/transformed --Learn how to deal with how you feel in this message from our weekend series: 50 Days of Transformation. This week Pastor Rick Warren focuses on transforming your emotional health. This series is centered around our Transformed study with Pastor Rick Warren at Saddleback Church. 

Pastor Rick Warren talks about how God can transform your emotional health by learning how to understand our emotions and how to manage unwanted feelings. You don't have to believe everything you think and you don't have to believe everything you feel. When you give your heart to Jesus, that includes your emotions. Learn how God can help you manage them. God didn't bring you here to watch everyone else's life be transformed--Join in at www.saddleback.com/transformed.

For service times & locations, visit saddleback.com. Connect with our online community at saddleback.com/online.

snippet.title: Transformed: How To Face The Fears That Ruin Relationships with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
www.saddleback.com/transformed --Learn how to change your life by transforming your relationships in this message from our weekend series: 50 Days of Transformation. This week Pastor Rick Warren focuses on transforming your relational health. This series is centered around our Transformed study with Pastor Rick Warren at Saddleback Church. 

This message will teach you how to defuse the fears that paralyze relationships. Pastor Rick Warren looks at Genesis 3:6-19 and the relationship between Adam and Eve; the very first human relationship on earth. In this story, we see the three basic fundamental fears that started in the first relationship. Pastor Rick talks about how our fears ruin relationships and how to transform your relationships. God didn't bring you here to watch everyone else's life be transformed--Join in at www.saddleback.com/transformed

snippet.title: Transformed: Transforming How I See & Use Money with Pastor Rick Warren
snippet.description:
www.saddleback.com/transformed --Learn how God can transform how you see and use money in this message from our series: 50 Days of Transformation. This week Pastor Rick Warren focuses on how God can transform your financial health. This series is centered around our Transformed study with Pastor Rick Warren at Saddleback Church. 

Pastor Rick Warren talks about the story of the shrewd manager in Luke 16:1-13. In this passage, we find that God's view of money is the exact opposite from the world's view of money. Pastor Rick shares what NOT to do with money and what to remember everyday when it comes to your finances. We must remember that it all comes from God and it is a tool to be used for God's purposes. God didn't bring you here to watch everyone else's life be transformed--Join in at www.saddleback.com/transformed

snippet.title: Learn How To Trust God's Timing with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com — Have you ever waited on God for something you desperately needed? Maybe it was a job, a spouse, a repaired relationship, a clean bill of health, or direction for your life. The Christmas story is also a story of waiting — the world was waiting for a Savior, and God answered that need by sending his Son, Jesus, to Earth at just the right time in history. In this special Christmas message, Pastor Rick Warren shows us how we can trust God’s perfect timing in our own lives. By looking at the example of Jesus’ birth, we can trust a God who overcomes our fear, teaches us patience, reminds us of his promises, and tells us to never give up. 














Continue the conversation online with our online community throughout the week during live services and weekly small groups: http://saddleback.com/online

Connect with Saddleback Church on Facebook: http://facebook.com/saddlebackchurch

snippet.title: Daring Faith: Daring To Wait On God with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith – No one ever said that waiting is easy. It takes patience, self-restraint, determination, and the hope that something good is yet to come. From that first gift under the Christmas tree to the family vacation marked on the calendar, we all face the challenge of waiting for that "next big thing" to be revealed. In an age of smart phones, quick fixes, and instant communication, waiting has become even more challenging. But waiting is an important part of life. You may be waiting on God to heal your disease, bring you employment, ease your burden, or answer your prayer. Sometimes though, God has to work on us before he works on our problems. In this sermon, Pastor Rick Warren details what do when when you're waiting on God, and how to be patient in the process.


To learn more about the Daring Faith study, visit: http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith

Watch our services on-demand throughout the week, or LIVE stream the service during the weekend: http://www.saddleback.com/online
























(Daring Faith) (Waiting on God) (unanswered prayer) (Prayer) (Rick Warren) (Saddleback Church) (Faith) (Delay) (Jesus) (God) (miracles)

snippet.title: Daring Faith: Learn What Happens When You Have Faith with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith – Faith and miracles go hand-in-hand. Pastor Rick Warren kicks off this 10-week series with a message about what faith is. You’ll discover that faith may not be what you think. It’s not a desire, a feeling, or a way of pretending that something is what it’s not. Instead, faith is a way of seeing — a way of looking at things from God’s point of view. Learn five problems that result from seeing with eyes of fear and six benefits of seeing with eyes of faith. You’ll find that living by faith opens the door for miracles, shrinks your problems, turns your dreams into reality, and more.


Start a small group or join one for the Daring Faith series. Learn more here: http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith 

Watch the Daring Faith sermons with us LIVE Online and connect with our Online Campus: http://www.saddleback.com/online

snippet.title: Daring Faith: How To Get Ready For A Miracle with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith – There are times in your life when you need God to turn a little into a lot. Whether it’s time, money, energy, or talent, you may need God to multiply what little you have. In part two of Daring Faith, Rick Warren uses the miraculous story of feeding the 5,000 to show how putting your faith in God turns a little into a lot. In this message, you’ll learn four ways to prepare for God to perform a miracle in your life. Discover how acting in faith and giving what little you have to God brings miraculous results to situations you thought were impossible or unsolvable.



Join a Small Group for the Daring Faith series here: http://saddleback.com/connect/smallgroups/join?curriculum=103

snippet.title: Daring Faith: Dare To Believe with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith – Will you dare to believe? That may be the most significant question you will ever be asked. This Easter, Pastor Rick Warren looks at what it really means to believe in Jesus. Discover that belief is much more than an acknowledgement of his existence — it’s about a relationship with him that turns on his power and creates change in your life. In this message, you’ll learn five things you can do to firmly trust and believe in Jesus. When you’re plugged into God’s strength and power, you’ll find forgiveness for everything you’ve ever done wrong, the invaluable gift of eternal life, your life’s purpose that will make an impact in the world, the ability to face any challenge that arises, and more.



For more information about our Daring Faith series, visit: http://www.saddleback.com/daringfaith

Watch our weekly messages Online and connect with our Online Community here: http://www.saddleback.com/Online

snippet.title: Learn What To Do When You're Pressured to Conform with Rick Warren
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/unshakable — How can you develop the courage to stand strong when your values are challenged? We are constantly being influenced by pressure from different directions, often from family and friends. But when someone in authority asks us to violate our principles, we don’t have to give in. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Rick Warren shares a message called When You’re Pressured to Conform. You’ll learn how to approach authority and maintain your integrity when you’re asked to violate your values or conscience.





Learn more about Daniel Plan at http://saddleback.com/danielplan.
Learn more about getting involved with Saddleback Student Ministries at http://saddleback.com/connect/ministry/student-ministries.


Connect with our Online Community throughout the week at http://saddleback.com/online.

snippet.description:
What do you do when you feel overwhelmed? One of the most common complaints of modern life is feeling overwhelmed. Pastor Rick Warren shares one of his favorite stories in the Bible about King Jehoshaphat to teach you five things to do when you are facing overwhelming circumstances. Learn how to pray like King Jehoshaphat did when he felt overwhelmed.

snippet.title: Learn How To Let Go Of Worry with Buddy Owens
snippet.description:
http://saddleback.com/ — We all worry. It affects our health, relationships, and can get in the way of achieving our goals and dreams. However, the Bible shows us that we can rely on God to provide for us and give peace, no matter our situation. In this message at Saddleback Church, Pastor Buddy Owens shares a message called How to Let Go of Worry. You’ll learn how you can overcome anxiety and find true peace in God’s plan for your life.


Connect with our online community during the week at http://saddleback.com/online.

snippet.description:

The same lies?” But if we really want to change our behavior, we have to change the way we think. It’s easy to conform to our old patterns of living, but God wants to transform our minds.

snippet.title: "Three Truths to Build Your Life On" with Buddy Owens
snippet.description: The cross of Jesus represents his crucifixion and resurrection — the price he paid for our forgiveness, and the promise of eternal life with him in heaven. However, as significant as that is, it is only a part of what Jesus accomplished. For this special Holy Week service, Pastor Buddy Owens shares three truths we learn from looking at the cross of Jesus, and how they can help us experience the fullness of God’s grace in our lives.

snippet.title: When You Are Tired of Failing
snippet.description:
Are you tired of failing to reach your goals? If you have a lot of good intentions but struggle to follow through, you won't want to miss church this week. We're learning the quality that can help us achieve every goal God puts on our hearts.


ABOUT THIS MESSAGE
What if becoming the person you want to be starts long before the moment you make a decision? Before you click "buy," before you take one more bite, or before you lash out at the people you love. Can the decisions you make today help you live the life you really want tomorrow? Let's learn together in our new message series, Pre-Decide. 

We’ve hand-picked articles, podcasts, and Bible Plans to help you learn how to make better choices in your life. Check out our Pre-Decide resources page to learn more! https://go2.lc/betterchoices-ytc

WE’RE OPEN
We’re continuing to monitor guidelines and best practices for gathering in a safe way. Learn more about everything we're doing to keep you safe and how you can help by using hand sanitizer, washing your hands often, and more: https://www.life.church/updates 

Find a time and attend a service with us: http://www.life.church/locations 

NEXT STEPS
Have you made a decision to follow Jesus? You may be wondering what’s next on your journey. We want to help! Let us guide you to your next steps in your walk with Christ: https://www.life.church/next 

ABOUT LIFE.CHURCH
Wherever you are in life, you have a purpose. Life.Church wants to help you find your next step. Our hope is that your journey will include joining us at a Life.Church location throughout the United States or globally online at https://www.live.life.church. Find locations, videos, and more info about us at https://www.life.church or download the Life.Church app at https://www.life.church/app.

snippet.title: Hope When You're Hurting
snippet.description:
Sometimes it can feel like the weight of the world is on your shoulders. From everything going on in the world to personal struggles, it’s easy to feel overwhelmed. No matter what you’re facing, church is a safe place to bring your doubts and fears. In this message, Pastor Craig is sharing how to find hope when you are hurting. 


ABOUT THIS MESSAGE
When you see God Is _____ what comes to mind? How can any of us really know what God's like? Too often, we view Him from our limited perspective, but it doesn't have to be that way. Together, let's discover how to fill that space with truth.

snippet.title: Where is God When You Hurt - Emotions Part 1
snippet.description:
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
Take a couple minutes to complete a short care check to tell us how you’re doing and how we can pray for you. We care about you, and we want to know how we can help. Complete the Care Check: https://go2.lc/carecheck-youtube 

When you’re grieving, when you’ve got hurt feelings, when you’re struggling, remember—Jesus hurt the same way you do. And He feels compassion for people who hurt. In this message, Pastor Craig Groeschel speaks to anyone feeling unsettled, depressed, anxious, or hopeless with a simple reminder: God sees you. Cast your hopes, your cares, and your hurt feelings on Him. He cares for you. 

ABOUT EMOTIONS
Joy. Sadness. Anger. Compassion. Emotions are electric. God has given each of us the capacity to feel deeply. And when we can better process our powerful emotions, we can start to understand how He will use them for His good. Learn more about the Emotions message series: https://www.life.church/emotions  

REOPENING
To ensure safety at all of our Life.Church locations, our weekend services have been redesigned to create a sanitary, touchless environment that allows for physical distancing. Learn more about everything we're doing to keep you safe and how you can help by using hand sanitizer, washing your hands often, and more:: https://www.life.church/updates

snippet.title: Reclaim Your Calling - Called
snippet.description:
Wondering how to find your purpose? It's not always easy, and when you find it, it will probably be even tougher to live it out. The moment you step into your calling, you step out of your comfort zone. But when you're called to a purpose, backing down isn't an option. Join Pastor Craig Groeschel to discover how reclaiming your calling may come at a cost—but it will also sustain you in the long run.

ABOUT LIFE.CHURCH
Wherever you are in life, you have a purpose. Life.Church wants to help you find your next step. Our hope is that your journey will include joining us at a Life.Church location throughout the United States or globally online at https://www.live.life.church. snippet.title: Stop Comparing Your Calling
snippet.description:
Your purpose is yours alone. God created you to live out your unique calling. No one else can do it for you. And you can’t live out anyone else’s. Join Pastor Craig Groeschel to see how when you start to compare your calling with someone else’s, you might find yourself disappointed, discouraged, or disillusioned with your life.

STAY CONNECTED
Even when we can’t meet in our physical locations, we’re still doing church. Stay updated with the latest news from Life.Church at https://www.life.church/stayconnected. You can also visit https://www.life.church/updates for the latest, or download the Life.Church app (https://www.life.church/app) and enable push notifications.

SUPPORT COVID-19 RESPONSE AND DIGITAL MISSIONS
You can designate a gift to Life.Church to go to coronavirus relief or to Digital Missions like the Church Online Platform! Your gift above the tithe helps meet immediate needs in your community and around the world and helps other churches to spread the Good News of Christ to people everywhere: https://www.life.church/giving 
 
DO CHURCH AT HOME
Churches in many countries are suspending regular in-person gatherings, but that doesn’t mean church is canceled. As followers of Jesus, we are the Church. Use this guide on having church at home to stay connected to your community: https://finds.life.church/church-at-home-guide/

snippet.title: When You’ve Had Enough - Anxious for Nothing Part 1 with Craig Groeschel
snippet.description:
When you’ve had enough of being anxious, you might make some mistakes. Learn from the biblical figure Elijah how to avoid running yourself into the ground, shutting people out, focusing on the negative, and forgetting God in your anxiety. God speaks in the whispers: don’t be anxious for nothing when you’ve had enough!

NEXT STEPS
Have you made a decision to follow Jesus? You may be wondering what’s next on your journey. We want to help! Let us guide you to your next steps in your walk with Christ: http://www.life.church/next 

ABOUT LIFE.CHURCH
Wherever you are in life, you have a purpose. Life.Church wants to help you find your next step. Our hope is that your journey will include joining us at a Life.Church location throughout the United States or globally online at https://www.live.life.church. Find locations, videos, and more info about us at https://www.life.church or download the Life.Church app at https://www.life.church/app. 

ABOUT ANXIOUS FOR NOTHING
Rejoice in the Lord always. I will say it again: Rejoice! Let your gentleness be evident to all. The Lord is near. Do not be anxious about anything, but in every situation, by prayer and petition, with thanksgiving, present your requests to God. And the peace of God, which transcends all understanding, will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus. Philippians 4:4-7 NIV

Nervous. Tense. Paralyzed by fear. You weren’t meant to live that way. The pressures of this world don’t have to consume you. If you’re looking for a better way, if you’re longing for peace—this message series is for you! Find related series, articles, discussion questions, and more: https://www.life.church/anxious

snippet.title: How to Overcome Anxiety - Anxious for Nothing Part 3 with Craig Groeschel
snippet.description:
When you’re wondering how to overcome anxiety, one of the best things you can do is shift your perspective. In this message, we’ll learn from the story of Paul and Silas, who were thrown into prison for their beliefs. But that didn’t stop them from keeping their focus on God’s provision. Anxiety will always try to keep your attention—join Pastor Craig Groeschel to see why a perspective of praise will help you discover true miracles as you’re learning how to overcome anxiety.

A GUIDE TO FINDING PEACE
What if you could be anxious for nothing—even though there are still things to be anxious about? Maybe you can. We asked a few people who have firsthand experience battling anxious thoughts or helping those who do to share a few things they’ve learned along the way. snippet.title: Dealing with Crippling Anxiety - Anxious for Nothing Part 4 with Craig Groeschel
snippet.description:
Dealing with crippling anxiety often makes it difficult to make decisions. We’re faced with so many choices and we’re so afraid of making a costly mistake, so we just can’t decide. In this message from Pastor Craig Groeschel, let’s learn to deal with crippling anxiety by surrounding ourselves with the right people, living for the right values, and listening to the right voices.
